Mpumalanga police have arrested suspects in connection with Esther Mahlangu's robbery attack. Courtesy of #DStv403 MBOMBELA -  Mpumalanga police have arrested suspects in connection with Esther Mahlangu's robbery attack. The 87-year-old Ndebele artist was attacked in her home in Siyabuswa last month. She was robbed of an undisclosed amount of money and a firearm. WATCH: Crime in SA | Mahlangu attacked, robbed of firearm, cash The suspects assaulted her before fleeing. Police put out a R50,000 reward for any information leading to arrests. The Mpumalanga Premier Refilwe Mtsweni-Tsipane will be visiting the family home on Thursday afternoon. #sapsMP #SAPS in Mpumalanga issue R50 000 reward for information about a suspect who robbed Dr Esther Mahlangu. Anyone with info to contact Col Ernest Maoka at 0823189843 or #CrimeStop on 0860010111 or using #MySAPSapp. SWhttps://t.co/BjX1My8WaM pic.twitter.com/56MGy0V1tR Media Advisory
